The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                 NATION BRIEFS
                              
	 Panaji, June 9 (PTI): A woman locked a leopard in her house on Monday in a village, 80km from Panaji, after it attacked her.           Rangawati Putu Velip, 45, was alone in her house. She was injured in the right eye but fought back and raised an alarm. The animal was captured later by forest officials.                   
	 Kapurthala (PTI): A case has been registered under the Representation of People Act, 1950, against Congress municipal councillor Namdev Arora and his family for enrolling in two constituencies. They had been included in the voter list from Bholanath constituency but got themselves enrolled in Kapurthala council from where Arora has won.                   
	 Bangalore (PTI): The army has started de-weeding of a lake in Bangalore to trace the body of a boy who fell into an open drain on May 31 during heavy rain. The army was asked to help in locating Abhisheks body from Hennur lake, where it could have got stuck, an official said.                   
	 Puducherry (PTI): A foreigner was arrested in Delhi on Tuesday for allegedly duping an engineer in Puducherry of Rs 3.53 lakh in an email lottery fraud. Konte Sandiakou of Mali allegedly sent a mail to the engineer telling him he had won $1million and a luxury car and should send a Rs 3.53 lakh to a bank as processing charges to receive the money.
                                                                                                                           
